## Problem
The bug was in the foster parent insertion logic in `HtmlTreeBuilder.java`. When parsing nested table structures with invalid content (like `<p>` tags inside tables), the parser would incorrectly place fostered content relative to already processed content like comments. Specifically, in the test case, `<p>Why am I here?</p>` was being placed before the comment `<!--Comment-->` in the final output, even though in the source document the comment came first.

## Root Cause
The `insertInFosterParent` method was using the default foster parenting logic without considering the specific context where nested tables exist within table cells, which led to incorrect document order when content was already inserted into the same parent context.

## Solution
I modified the `insertInFosterParent` method to detect when the fostered content should be placed directly into a table cell (`td` or `th`) element instead of being placed before the table element. This preserves the document order of content within table cells.

## The Fix
```java
void insertInFosterParent(Node in) {
    Element fosterParent;
    Element lastTable = getFromStack("table");
    boolean isLastTableParent = false;
    if (lastTable != null) {
        // Check if we're in a table cell context (td/th) and try to preserve document order
        Element tableParent = lastTable.parent();
        if (tableParent != null) {
            // If the table is directly in a cell, try to insert into the cell to maintain order
            if ("td".equals(tableParent.nodeName()) || "th".equals(tableParent.nodeName())) {
                tableParent.appendChild(in);
                return;
            }
        }

        // Original logic for other cases
        if (lastTable.parent() != null) {
            fosterParent = lastTable.parent();
            isLastTableParent = true;
        } else
            fosterParent = aboveOnStack(lastTable);
    } else { // no table == frag
        fosterParent = stack.get(0);
    }

    if (isLastTableParent) {
        Validate.notNull(lastTable); // last table cannot be null by this point.
        lastTable.before(in);
    }
    else
        fosterParent.appendChild(in);
}
```

